        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Add native Telegram draft streaming support",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\n- Add native Telegram `sendMessageDraft` streaming for DM answer text, producing smooth typing animation instead of choppy `editMessageText` edits\r\n- Gated behind `channels.telegram.streaming.nativeTransport: true` + `mode: \"partial\"` + private chat scope; groups always fall back to edit-based streaming\r\n- Extract shared draft utilities (`resolveSendMessageDraftApi`, `allocateTelegramDraftId`, `normalizeDraftText`) into `native-draft-api.ts`, reused by both tool-progress and answer draft modules\r\n\r\n## How it works\r\n\r\nWhen `nativeTransport` is enabled, DM answer streaming uses `sendMessageDraft` with a unique `draftId` for live preview updates. On finalization, `sendMessage` persists the final text. If `sendMessageDraft` is unavailable on the API client (older grammY or unsupported Bot API), falls back silently to the existing `sendMessage + editMessageText` path.\r\n\r\nEdge cases addressed (these caused the previous maintainer note against reintroducing draft streaming):\r\n- **30s draft expiry**: throttle loop fires every ~1s; tool calls pause answer draft and use a separate `draftId`\r\n- **Duplicate finals**: `streamState.final` + `lane.finalized` flags prevent double materialization; `sendMessage` in `stop()` is the exclusive final path\r\n- **Draft→final flash**: `sendMessage` fires immediately after last draft; draft expires naturally\r\n- **>4096 chars**: draft truncated during streaming; full text delivered via `sendMessage`\r\n- **Media/buttons**: text finalizes via stream, media sends separately (existing lane deliverer pattern)\r\n- **Quote replies**: already skip preview streaming when `hasTelegramQuoteReply` is true\r\n\r\n## Test plan\r\n\r\n- [x] `native-draft-api.test.ts` — 8 tests: API resolution, draft ID allocation, text normalization\r\n- [x] `native-answer-draft.test.ts` — 15 tests: unavailable API fallback, draft updates, stop/materialize lifecycle, ephemeral clear, forceNewMessage, >4096 truncation, error recovery, thread/reply params, dedup, minInitialChars debounce, renderText parse mode\r\n- [x] `native-tool-progress-draft.test.ts` — 3 tests pass (regression check after shared utility extraction)\r\n- [x] `config-schema.test.ts` — 41 tests pass (schema accepts `nativeTransport`)\r\n- [x] `draft-stream.test.ts` — 32 tests pass (no regression to edit-based streaming)\r\n- [x] `bot-message-dispatch.test.ts` — 80 tests pass (dispatch wiring)\r\n- [x] Full Telegram extension suite — 1826 tests across 122 files, zero failures\r\n- [ ] Real Telegram proof: DM streaming with `nativeTransport: true` on bot-to-bot QA lane",
        "branch": "feat/telegram-native-answer-streaming",
